Title: The Phase of the Scattering Matrix
Authors: Jos\'e M. Gracia-Bond\'{\i}a (Univ. Complutense de Madrid)
Comments: 13 pages, PlainTeX
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B482 (2000) 315-322
\\
  Vacuum polarization in external fields is treated by way of calculating -
exactly and then perturbatively - the phase of the quantum scattering matrix in
the Shale-Stinespring approach to field theory. The link between the
Shale-Stinespring method and the Epstein-Glaser renormalization procedure is
highlighted.
